A =\begin{bmatrix} a & b\\c & d\\\end{bmatrix}
 X = \begin{bmatrix} x\\ y\\ \end{bmatrix}
B = \begin{bmatrix} e\\ f\\ \end{bmatrix}
ad-bc \neq0
AX = B
\begin{cases} ax + by = e,\\cx + dy = f.\\\end{cases}
x = \frac{bf-de}{ad-bc}
y = \frac{af-ce}{ad-bc}
A
2 \times 2
\frac cd
\begin{bmatrix} a & b & e\\c & d & f\\\end{bmatrix}\to\begin{bmatrix} a & b & e\\\frac cd & 1 & \frac fd\\\end{bmatrix}\to \begin{bmatrix} a-\frac {bc}d & 0 & e-\frac{bf}d\\\frac cd & 1 & \frac fd\\\end{bmatrix}\to \begin{bmatrix} 1 & 0 & (e-\frac{bf}d)\frac d{ad-bc}\\\frac cd & 1 & \frac fd\\\end{bmatrix}
